-- Buzzi Unicem's Shares Gain in Milan Trading After Equita Upgrade to `Buy'
-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 2010-10-04T08:38:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/buzzi-unicem-s-shares-gain-in-milan-trading-after-equita-upgrade-to-buy-.html
Buzzi Unicem SpA  gained as much as
2.8 percent in Milan trading as Equita Sim upgraded Italy’s
second-biggest cement maker to “buy” from “hold.”  The brokerage, which said that cement prices in Italy have
stopped falling and cement volumes show signs that they will
rebound, also added the stock to its “main portfolio” with a
weight of 150 basis points.  Equita lifted its price estimate on the ordinary shares by
7 percent to 10 euros and on the savings shares by 4 percent to
5.7 euros.  The common shares rose 1.9 percent to 7.99 euros as of
10:30 a.m. local time, the best performance on Italy’s  FTSE MIB
Index . The savings shares increased 2.1 percent to 4.58 euros
after gaining as much as 2.8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
